 {"id":"franken_networkx-xtkh","title":"Port complete_multipartite_graph iterable partitions + subset attrs","description":"fnx.complete_multipartite_graph currently (1) drops the 'subset' node attribute that NetworkX sets on every node (partition index), and (2) rejects iterables as partitions even though nx.complete_multipartite_graph accepts either all ints (partition sizes) or all iterables (explicit node labels per partition). Rewrite the Python wrapper on top of the existing Rust fast path to: match nx's all-ints vs all-iterables detection, reject mixed-type inputs with the exact NetworkX error, add subset=<partition-index> to every node, and preserve the existing Rust path for the sizes-only case. Add parity tests covering sizes-only, list-of-iterables, zero-sized partition, mixed-type rejection, and subset attribute presence.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"claude-fnx-port","created_at":"2026-04-20T21:29:34.528411195Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-20T21:32:03.644271222Z","closed_at":"2026-04-20T21:32:03.641534179Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-xv8j","title":"[C4] Wire 12 reference algorithms through CGSE","description":"**Track:** C. **Priority:** P0. **Type:** feature.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-09T00:23:26.167651233Z","updated_at":"2026-04-10T02:24:30.807447018Z","closed_at":"2026-04-10T02:24:30.807255395Z","close_reason":"Wired all 12 reference algorithms through CGSE: Dijkstra, BellmanFord, Bfs, Dfs, MaxWeightMatching, MinWeightMatching, ConnectedComponents, StronglyConnectedComponents, Kruskal, Prim, EulerianCircuit, TopologicalSort. Each algorithm now calls cgse_begin/cgse_record_decision/cgse_publish to emit ComplexityWitness records.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"franken_networkx-xv8j","depends_on_id":"franken_networkx-ckpt","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-09T00:24:41.484423285Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
